etymology.description: 𠧪 is a variant form of 卣(卣) (yǒu, "a kind of wine vessel") -> pictogram with 土(earth) in bronze inscriptions, later changed to 仌 in seal script -> unrelated to 鹵(鹵) (lǔ, "bag of salt")
etymology.interpretation: 𠧪 is an ancient variant of 卣(卣), which depicts a type of vessel for holding wine. This character evolved over time, with the enclosed component changing from 土 to 仌 in different script styles.

examples.chinese: 这篇文章中提到了𠧪(這篇文章中提到了𠧪)，引发了学者讨论(引發了學者討論)。
examples.pinyin: Zhè piān wénzhāng zhōng tí dào le yín, yǐn fā le xuézhě tǎolùn.
examples.english: The article mentioned Yin, sparking a discussion among scholars.

examples.chinese: 博物馆展出罕见的𠧪文物(博物館展出罕見的𠧪文物)。
examples.pinyin: Bówùguǎn zhǎnchū hǎnjiàn de yín wénwù.
examples.english: The museum exhibited the rare Yin artifact.
